03/12/2008
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO Secretary-General Jaap de Hoop Scheffer hopes to see Albania and Croatia become full members of the Alliance during its April summit in Strasbourg-Kehl. At a meeting Tuesday (December 2nd) of foreign ministers from NATO member countries, de Hoop Scheffer urged the countries to ratify the membership bids of Albania and Croatia. Albanian Foreign Minister Lulzim Basha, who attended the Brussels meeting, said about ten countries have signed the protocols and the others promise to act quickly. They "have made it clear that there will be no delays for Albania and Croatia to have their seats at the next summit", Basha said. (Alsat, Klan, Top News, VOA - 03/12/08)
